FBIS4-57052 "drlat092_o_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-092 Daily Report 12 May 1994 Colombia Foreign Minister Confirms Citizenship of Paul Ames Foreign Minister Confirms Citizenship of Paul Ames PA1205021294 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 12 May 94 PA1205021294 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Spanish BFN [From the "24 Hours Newscast"] [Text] Paul Ames, the son of Maria del Rosario Casas who is under arrest in the United States charged with espionage, will be granted Colombian citizenship. This afternoon, Foreign Minister Noemi Sanin confirmed this in Manizales. [Begin Sanin recording] Yesterday, we were visited by Maria Casas' mother. She explained her daughter's situation. We are studying her petition to reacquire citizenship and we have promised to grant it in the case of her son because he is an innocent person who has Colombian blood and we should all protect this young and innocent child. [end recording]
